- Teams that have never been visitors are considered to be at the base of the hierarchy (level 1);
- The hierarchy is built recursively, with each subsequent level including teams that have visited teams from the previous level;
- Win percentage is calculated as the total wins divided by the total number of games played (wins + losses);
- The rank within each level is determined by the win percentage, with the highest win percentage ranking first;
- Cumulative wins are the sum of total wins up to that team within the same level.

